  "response_text": "The mean household initial risk attitude remains constant at approximately 0.0074 throughout the entire 100-step simulation period. This metric shows no temporal variation, maintaining identical values from the initial time step through to the conclusion of the simulation. Across 30 repeated simulation runs, the aggregate mean exhibits no fluctuation, with zero variance and no detectable trends in any temporal window.\n\nThis static pattern indicates that the initial risk attitude functions as a fixed attribute assigned to social learning agents at the simulation's outset, representing their baseline disposition to deviate from recommended livestock numbers. Unlike dynamic variables that might adjust based on pasture conditions, rainfall variability, or accumulated experience, this parameter serves as an unchanging reference point that persists despite the ecological and decision-making dynamics occurring within the model."
}

